div1.p:
The 2d Count charged him with forging an acceptance to the said bill, purporting to be the acceptance of the said
Edward Russel
, Esq;

To
Edw. Russel
, Esq;

(The record of the conviction of
James Leppenwell
for stealing the goods was read in court.)

"The prisoner, in his defence, said that he was extremely drunk; that he staid all night; that he hung his great coat up when he came home, and that he took it down to brush, a few hours before the prosecutor came to search his house, and then he found the knives and forks in his pocket. He called
Thomas Newman
, who had known him a great many years;
John Simpson
, Fourteen or fifteen years;
William Duet
fourteen years;
Henry Doughty
, seven years;
David Easton
, seven years; - Wild, seven years;
William Potter
, ten years; and
Thomas Cornwall
some time; who gave him an unexceptionable character."
